Package kr.co.elpusk.android.liblpu237

Interface ApiInterface

public interface ApiInterface
All API class must be implement these interfaces.
API user have to use methods of this interface only.
Don't use a method of this interface implementer directly. In version 1.0.0, API supports only single device using.
Since:
1.0.0

    • Open

      UsbDevHandle Open(String sPath)
      open lpu237 If open is succeed,
      you must call SetupForRead() or ToolsMsrStartGetSetting() before using another method.
      SetupForRead() read a minimum system parameter for reading msr or ibutton.
      ToolsMsrStartGetSetting() read all most system parameter for changing system parameters.
      Parameters:
      sPath - lpu237 device path.
      you can get by UsbDevHandle.get_path().
      Returns:
      UsbDevHandle

    • SetupForRead

      boolean SetupForRead(UsbDevHandle handle, boolean bChangeInterfaceToHid)
      setup for reading msr or ibutton.(get minimum system parameters, and setting)
      Parameters:
      handle - the UsbDevHandle instance that is used in Open() method.
      bChangeInterfaceToHid - true -> If current interface isn't usb hid vendor, change to usb hid vendor and apply.
      false -> No Thank you
      Returns:
      true -> success.
      false -> fail

    • ToolsMsrGetActiveAndValiedInterface

      int[] ToolsMsrGetActiveAndValiedInterface(UsbDevHandle handle)
      Get the active and valid interface from loaded lpu237 system parameters.
      this function can use after ToolsMsrStartGetSetting() is Done.
      Parameters:
      handle - the UsbDevHandle instance that is used in Open() method.
      Returns:
      int[] the the first item is active interface, from the second item is valid interfaces.
      0 -> usb keyboard interface.
      1 -> usb hid vendor interface.
      2 -> usb virtual COM interface.
      10 -> real UART interface.
